#README 
SA-Orange-Titan-ThreatIntelligence

#Installation
1) Open the Apps page on the search head.
2) Select install app from file. (or from Splunkbase)
3) Be sure to check the "upgrade" option.
4) Navigate to the setup view of the app (Either via the Apps > Set Up option or via the redirect)
5) Set up a configuration according to the guide and optionally proxy.
6) Click complete setup.
7) Issue a search for sourcetype="threatlist:titan:downloadinfo"
You should now be able to see that the python script has done its work.
Optionally, configure the scripted input under Settings > Data Inputs > Scripts > titan_wrapper.py to a desired interval.

#Features
Enables easy ingestion of Titan TI data into Splunk
Logs to standard output for capture in Splunk
Rudimentary error handling.
Proxy support, configurable from the setup page.


#Requirements
1) API token from Orange Cyberdefense

#Supported versions
This app supports all version from 6.5 and on as of writing.
In the case of Splunk Cloud installations, this app needs to be installed on a heavy-forwarder instead of the SH, with forwarding of the created csv files to the SH.

#Support
If you need help, contact cdc@orangecyberdefense.com
